    ("T234", "PLAN: persistent account-role marker (athlete vs coach) + role-aware routing across web + mobile for every signup/sign-in scenario incl. athlete->coach upgrade; ends the shared signup_checkpoint conflict", "Coach/Auth", "Web+Mobile+DB", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-12 (frustrated by repeated signup/routing seams T229..T233): wants ONE persistent marker so sign-in/routing is correct in every situation. Their stated rules: athlete -> download-app (web) / app (mobile); coach -> portal; mid-signup athlete -> download-app on web, coach -> resume on web; an athlete upgrading to coach keeps working on mobile (athlete is complete+validated) but does a FRESH coach signup on web that SKIPS already-validated steps (prefilled + back-editable), role flips to coach only when the final step completes (athlete data persists). Root cause behind the seams: signup_checkpoint is ONE shared column for both journeys (T231 put coach-only 'plan'/'stripe' values in it; mobile CHECKPOINT_RANK has no such keys).",
     "APPROVED 2026-06-12 (user: 'go'). Marker = profiles.account_marker A|AC|C (NO separate coach_signup_step -- the marker itself gates which journey each platform interprets, so the shared signup_checkpoint never cross-contaminates). A=athlete(mobile); C=coach(web new email, set at init-profile-checkpoint); AC=existing athlete converting (stamped in coach Signup detectFlow when a marker-A user reaches coach signup); AC|C settle->C at coach welcome-end. Routing via web/src/lib/roleRouting.js roleHomePath(): A->/app(download); C|AC + active sub->/portal; C|AC no sub->/signup(resume coach signup); main-host admin->/admin/overview. PHASE 1 (DB account_marker + backfill: 11 A, 1 C) DONE+applied. PHASE 2 (roleHomePath resolver; RoleRouter/NotFound/Auth.jsx rewrite; /app added to coach host; init-profile-checkpoint=C [edge fn v9]; detectFlow AC-stamp; welcome-end=C) DONE+deployed. PHASE 3 DONE+deployed live (index-Bl3j42y1.js): check_account_status RPC (SECURITY DEFINER, anon, returns only exists+marker) + EmailScreen in-flow phases (email->confirm 'You already have an athlete account'->password verify; correct password = A->AC + prefill + jump past validated steps; marker C emails -> 'sign in' prompt; RPC failure fails OPEN to the old signUp-time interstitial) + shouldSkip('password') when email===verifiedEmail. PHASE 4 DONE: mobile Profile.account_marker type; sign-up hydration intercepts C|AC + !onboarded -> new (auth)/coach-pending.tsx ('Finish on the web' opens coach.myrxfit.com / 'Switch to an athlete account' -> marker A + plan|stripe checkpoint remapped to photo -> athlete resume / sign-out link). tsc clean. PHASE 5 VERIFIED on live build via Chrome: signed-out coach landing OK; seeded-journey email step -> typed the real athlete email -> RPC 'Checking...' -> confirm step rendered -> Yes -> password-verify step rendered; STOPPED before password (assistant cannot enter credentials) + DB confirmed untouched (marker stayed A). Also cleaned pre-T234 residue: personal athlete profile had coach-only checkpoint 'plan' -> reset to welcome-end. Docs: docs/context/coach-platform.md new 'account_marker A/AC/C state machine' section + superseded post-sign-in routing note. USER STILL TO TEST: full password-verified conversion (A->AC->plan), new-coach C signup end-to-end, mobile coach-pending screen on device (Metro reload pushed).",
     "web/src/lib/roleRouting.js (new) ; web/src/App.jsx (RoleRouter/NotFound/import/+app route) ; web/src/pages/Auth.jsx (post-sign-in) ; web/src/pages/coach/Signup.jsx (detectFlow select + AC stamp + welcome-end C) ; supabase/functions/init-profile-checkpoint (account_marker C) ; supabase/migrations/20260612_add_profiles_account_marker.sql",
     "2026-06-12"),
