    ("T143", "Plan-management / coaching-state wiring audit -- 'Self-managed' client wrongly shows 'plan pending from coach' on mobile; trace EVERY scenario", "Coaching", "Mobile+Web", "Done",
     "User 2026-06-09: Test Client is set to Self-managed in the coach portal (CoachManageChip -> macros_managed_by_coach=false) but the mobile Calories card shows 'Your plan is on its way' (the coach-will-author PendingView) instead of letting the client set up their own plan. Likely a T139 regression: canEditPlanHere went from '!isStaff && (isSelfCoached || !macrosManagedByCoach)' to '!isStaff && isSelfCoached', which IGNORES the coach's Self-managed handback -- a coached-but-handed-back client is stuck read-only, and the coach also loses calorie_plans WRITE via RLS when macros_managed_by_coach=false (potential 'nobody can author the plan' dead-zone). User: can't test every scenario by hand -- wants a full line-by-line trace of the coaching-state + plan-management + tier data path across EVERY combination, then a resolution plan (plan first, do NOT implement yet).",
     "AUDIT COMPLETE 2026-06-09 (4 parallel agents; traced mobile + web + RLS + DB). ROOT CAUSE = two different 'self-managed' switches conflated: (1) DB trigger sync_is_self_coached() pins is_self_coached := (coach_id IS NULL), so a coached client is PERMANENTLY is_self_coached=false no matter the coach's handback; (2) the coach 'Self-managed' chip writes ONLY macros_managed_by_coach=false (leaves coach_id); (3) T139 made the mobile gate canEditPlanHere = !isStaff && isSelfCoached -- never reads macros_managed_by_coach, so the handback does nothing for the client; (4) calorie_plans client-write RLS ('Users insert/update own plan when self-coached') also requires is_self_coached=true -> a handed-back client literally cannot save; (5) after handback the coach's web editor ALSO hides (canManageMacros = macros_managed_by_coach===true) -> NOBODY can author -> 'Your plan is on its way' forever. Default macros_managed_by_coach=false means every attached client looks handed-back by default. SEPARATE bugs found: coach-managed clients on maintenance get 'coach hasn't set a goal' (isMaintenancePhase requires canEditPlanHere -> C1 maintenance UI unreachable for managed clients); CoachClientDetail.jsx:415 computes coachActive via an inline block-list on the COACH's own status instead of the client_has_active_coach RPC (diverges for null/paused/unpaid + ignores coach.deactivated_at -> coach can see a client at fullrx that the client's app shows at free); stale b2c-tier JSDoc (AuthContext.tsx:181-185, CoachClientDetail.jsx:410-411) still say Heart=corerx. NOTE: live calorie_plans roster RLS (Coaches insert/update roster) is gated on coach_id only (NOT the macros flag) and is NOT in git migrations. RESOLVED 2026-06-09 via Option 1 (user picked #1: 'Self-managed' = the client manages their own plan even while rostered; new attached clients DEFAULT to coach-managed/read-only). FIXES: (mobile) canEditPlanHere = !isStaff && (isSelfCoached || !macrosManagedByCoach) + goalReached re-coupled to canEditPlanHere -- reverts the T139 isSelfCoached-only gate; (RLS) migration t143_client_writes_plan_when_self_managed lets a client INSERT/UPDATE their own calorie_plans when macros_managed_by_coach=false (covers self-coached + handed-back); (RLS) migration t143_macros_managed_default_on_coach_attach adds a trigger that sets macros_managed_by_coach=true on coach_id NULL->set (new attaches read-only by default) and false on detach; (BACKFILL per user) Test Client + Mirvatt -> coach/admin-managed, Motaz re-linked to admin + managed, everyone else already self-coached, Ahmad Saadeh HELD (currently linked to admin but the user didn't name him -- awaiting OK to unlink); (item 5) CoachClientDetail coachActive switched from a block-list on the coach's own status to the client_has_active_coach RPC allow-list (trialing/active/past_due | superuser) so the coach view matches the client's own app; (item 7) stale Heart=corerx comments fixed (AuthContext, CoachClientDetail). Item 6 (maintenance-misroute copy) split to T144. Coach broad-roster calorie_plans write RLS still un-gated on the macros flag (benign, UI-gated) -- noted as future cleanup. Mobile reloaded; web live index-h4hT12hN.js.",
     "mobile/app/(app)/calories.tsx (canEditPlanHere + goalReached); mobile/src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx (comment); web/src/pages/coach/CoachClientDetail.jsx (coachActive + comment); migrations t143_client_writes_plan_when_self_managed + t143_macros_managed_default_on_coach_attach; profiles backfill (Test Client/Mirvatt/Motaz)",
     "2026-06-09"),

    ("T144", "Calories goal card -- coach-managed client on a pure-maintenance plan sees 'your coach hasn't set a goal weight' instead of an 'On maintenance' read-only message", "Calories", "Mobile", "Done",
     "Found in the T143 audit (item 6). For a coach/admin-managed client (macros_managed_by_coach=true -> canEditPlanHere=false) whose plan is a pure maintenance phase (energy_balance_pct ~= 0 AND start ~= goal), the maintenance UI (CurrentWeightGoal branch C1) is skipped because isMaintenancePhase REQUIRES canEditPlanHere, so the card falls through to the no-goal fallback C2c and shows 'Your coach hasn't set a goal weight for this phase yet' -- wrong (the coach DID set a maintenance plan). Option 1 (T143) already fixed this for self-coached + handed-back clients (they now have canEditPlanHere=true -> reach C1).",
     "DONE + reloaded 2026-06-09. Removed the canEditPlanHere requirement from isMaintenancePhase so the maintenance state is detected for ANY client on a pct~=0 + start~=goal plan. The edit affordances were ALREADY separately gated on canEditPlanHere (headerRow pencil + planSummaryRow), so a coach-managed client now sees the 'HOLDING AT X / on maintenance' card READ-ONLY (no pencil, no chips) instead of the wrong 'your coach hasn't set a goal weight' fallback; self-coached / handed-back clients still get the editable version. One-line gate change + stale-comment refresh.",
     "mobile/app/(app)/calories.tsx (isMaintenancePhase gate)",
     "2026-06-09"),

