     "User 2026-06-11 (live test as Test Coach on /coach/profile -> Billing): tapped 'Manage plan' -> red 'Edge Function returned a non-2xx status code'. DIAGNOSED two things. (1) The Test Coach (id dc2fa45f-f51f-4046-a628-2a6aab5917be) is a LEGACY pre-T194 account -- is_coach=true + coach_subscription_status='trialing' + tier='elite' were written DIRECTLY by the OLD pre-grant-flip coach-signup, but coach_stripe_customer_id is NULL and coach_subscriptions has 0 rows (no real Stripe checkout ever completed; the column didn't exist back then). So coach-billing-portal correctly returns 400 no_customer ('No billing account found for your coach plan.') -- genuinely no Stripe customer to manage. Its coach_trial_ends_at is 2026-06-09 (past) yet status is still 'trialing' because no Stripe webhook ever fires for a fake sub, so it just sits live -- which is how it still passes the gate. A coach created through the NEW flow always has coach_stripe_customer_id (coach-signup stores it pre-checkout), so they won't hit this. (2) REAL UX BUG: the web openBillingPortal handler surfaced supabase-js's generic FunctionsHttpError.message instead of our function's friendly { error } body -- which lives on error.context (the Response), not error.message.",
     "DONE 2026-06-11 (web, rebuilt + redeployed): CoachProfile.openBillingPortal now reads error.context.json() and shows body.error (e.g. 'No billing account found for your coach plan.') instead of the generic wrapper message. NOTE the legacy Test Coach can't test Manage plan (no Stripe customer); to test it end-to-end the user does a FRESH coach signup (new flow creates the real Stripe customer + sub via test card 4242) AND must enable the Stripe Customer Portal in the dashboard. The Test Coach's legacy fake-trial state gets cleared by the step-10 wipe.",
